Package: GHformats
Type: Package
Title: Templates for HTML and PDF/LaTeX Output Formats Designed for Guardant Health
Version: 1.0.0.9000
Date: 2022-9-06
Authors@R: c(
    person("Daniel", "Hintz", email="dhintz@guardanthealth.com",
        role=c("aut","cre")),
    person("Saskia", "Otto",
        role="aut",
        comment="Original author of UHHformats"))
Maintainer: Daniel Hintz <dhintz@guardanthealth.com>
URL: https://github.com/gh-dhintz/GHformats
Description: R Markdown and Quarto templates for HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents, which are used
    within Guardant Health. These include templates for reports, analyses,
    and conversions to Jupyter Notebooks. The package aims to encourage
    reproducible research using simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of the R code to
    produce plots and analyses as well. This package is a derivative work based on
    'UHHformats' by Saskia Otto (https://github.com/uham-bio/UHHformats),
    adapted and rebranded for Guardant Health. Many templates are inspired by or based on other
    packages such as 'rmdformats', 'ireports' or 'rmd2jupyter'.
